CompanyDescription.label: Company Description
CompanyDescription.value: MetLife-once a mutual company before the 2000 demutualization-is the largest life insurer in the U.S. by assets and provides a variety of insurance and financial services products. Outside the United States, MetLife operates in Japan and more than 40 countries in Latin America, Asia-Pacific, Europe, and the Middle East.
